{
  "texts": [
    "In particular, the real dimension of S r B is 2r.For d = g -1, N d is a finite set of order 2 2g.",
    "The corresponding representations ρ: π 1 (B) → SL 2 (R) are the 2 2g -possible lifts of the uniformising representation π 1 (B) → PSL 2 (R), and the corresponding solitons are homogeneous (cf.",
    "Example 3.9).If d = 0, the condition tr Φ 2 = 0 forces Φ = 0.",
    "Indeed, if β = 0, then L -1 is a Φ-invariant sub-bundle with deg L -1 = 0, so E = L ⊕ L -1 must split as a sum of Higgs line bundles of degree 0.",
    "The only way this is possible is if γ = 0."
  ]
}